{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["RBD Convex Proxy"], "type": "title", "extent": [48, 69], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [69, 183], "text": ["Creates a number of rigid bodies from SOP geometry, which use proxy geometry from a convex decomposition."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [183, 419], "text": ["This tool uses the ", {"text": ["Convex Decomposition SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/convexdecomposition", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/convexdecomposition"}, " to generate proxy geometry for the RBD objects. A compound collision shape built from several convex hulls can be much faster to simulate for concave geometry."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [419, 918], "text": ["This tool is similar to the ", {"text": ["RBD Sphere Proxy tool"], "fullpath": "/shelf/rbdsphereproxy", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/shelf/rbdsphereproxy"}, " on the ", {"text": ["Rigid Bodies"], "type": "ui"}, " shelf. However, instead of using proxy geometry composed of spheres, it preserves hard edges and creates more accurate shapes. ", {"text": ["RBD Sphere Proxy tool"], "fullpath": "/shelf/rbdsphereproxy", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/shelf/rbdsphereproxy"}, " is very lightweight and fast, which is useful for background objects where you don\u2019t mind rounded out corners as a tradeoff for speed. Convex Decomposition is useful for more complex or foreground objects with many hard edges."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [918, 960], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/rbdconvexproxy.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/shelf/rbdconvexproxy.png"}]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [1001, 1056], "text": ["Select the geometry to convert to RBD objects."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [1056, 1164], "text": ["Optionally, define the pieces to be fractured. For example, using the ", {"text": ["Shatter tool"], "fullpath": "/shelf/shatter", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/shelf/shatter"}, "."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [1164, 1265], "text": ["Click the ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SHELF/rbdconvexproxy", "scheme": "Icon", "type": "link", "value": "SHELF/rbdconvexproxy"}, {"text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/rbdconvexproxy", "scheme": "Shelf", "type": "link", "value": "rbdconvexproxy"}, " tool on the ", {"text": ["Rigid Bodies"], "type": "ui"}, " tab."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [1265, 1419], "text": ["Modify the parameters of the ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/convexdecomposition", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/convexdecomposition"}, " SOP, if necessary, to adjust the concavity threshold used by the convex decomposition."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [1419, 1567], "text": ["Switch the display flag to the ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/xformpieces", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/xformpieces"}, " SOP to see the original geometry transformed based on the motion of the proxy objects."]}], "container": true, "type": "ord_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Using RBD Convex Proxy"], "extent": [960, 1001], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": "includeme"}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [1567, 1745], "text": ["For specific parameter help see the ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/DOP/rbdpackedobject", "scheme": "Icon", "type": "link", "value": "DOP/rbdpackedobject"}, {"text": ["RBD Packed Object"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/rbdpackedobject", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/dop/rbdpackedobject"}, " or ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SOP/convexdecomposition", "scheme": "Icon", "type": "link", "value": "SOP/convexdecomposition"}, {"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/convexdecomposition", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/convexdecomposition"}, " help."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1754, 1784], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/bulletrbdsolver", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/dop/bulletrbdsolver"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1784, 1813], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/rbdpackedobject", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/dop/rbdpackedobject"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1813, 1846], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/convexdecomposition", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/convexdecomposition"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1846, 1871], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/xformpieces", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/xformpieces"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [1745, 1754], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "summary": ["Creates a number of rigid bodies from SOP geometry, which use proxy geometry from a convex decomposition."], "type": "root", "attrs": {"tags": "rigidbodies", "icon": "SHELF/rbdconvexproxy"}, "title": ["RBD Convex Proxy"]}